#
water <- water %>% 
  group_by(Potability) %>%
  mutate(across(where(is.numeric), ~if_else(is.na(.), mean(., na.rm = T), as.numeric(.)))) %>% ungroup()

MODELING

#
water$ph <- scale(water$ph)
water$Hardness <- scale(water$Hardness)
water$Solids <- scale(water$Solids)
water$Chloramines <- scale(water$Chloramines)
water$Sulfate <- scale(water$Sulfate)
water$Conductivity <- scale(water$Conductivity)
water$Organic_carbon <- scale(water$Organic_carbon)
water$Trihalomethanes <- scale(water$Trihalomethanes)
water$Turbidity <- scale(water$Turbidity)
#
set.seed(20220412)
train_ind <- sample(nrow(water), floor(0.75 * nrow(water)))
trainwater <- water[train_ind, ]
testwater <- water[-train_ind,]

PCA

#PCA

waterpca <- prcomp(trainwater[,c(1:9)],
                              center=T,
                              scale=T)


cumulative.props <- cumsum((waterpca$sdev)^2 / sum((waterpca$sdev)^2))
cumulative.props
## [1] 0.1378542 0.2647366 0.3824375 0.4963695 0.6074053 0.7145094 0.8180803
## [8] 0.9147136 1.0000000
water.pca.plot <- autoplot(waterpca,
                          data = trainwater,

                          )
water.pca.plot

#log.model

for (i in 1:nrow(testwater)) {
  if(log.pred[i]>=0.5){
    log.pred[i] <- 1
  }
  else{
    log.pred[i] <- 0
  }
}
log.pred <- as.factor(log.pred)
levels(log.pred) <- c("0","1")

confusionMatrix(testwater$Potability,log.pred)
